Language name: BOBO-FING
Language number: 4138
Alternate names: Sya, Bobo
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Mande
Comments: Bobo is spoken in western Burkina-Faso (formerly 
Upper Volta). The language has 3 level tones, which 
combine into four contours (HL, ML, LH, LM).
Sources: 

le Bris, P. and Prost, A. 1981. Dictionnaire Bobo-Fing 
(precedee d'une introduction grammaticale et suivi d'un 
lexique francais). SELAF, Paris.

Morse, M.L.A. 1976. A Sketch of the Phonology and 
Morphology of Bobo (Upper Volta). PhD thesis, Columbia 
University, New York.